- 6 Aug 2018. 13:22 WAT. DRC: No reported case of Ebola in Ituri, says governor Abdallah Pene Mbaka
[Radio Okapi, in French, machine trans., edited]
https://www.radiookapi.net/2018/08/06/actualite/sante/rdc-aucun-cas-declare-debola-en-ituri-selon-le-gouverneur-abdallah-pene

Contrary to the rumors circulating about possible cases of Ebola in Ituri, no case is declared there, assured the governor of this province Abdallah Pene Mbaka. During a press briefing held on Sun 5 Aug, he still invited the people to wash their hands, avoid contact with people who are suspicious or who died of this disease.

"The Ebola outbreak is not declared in Ituri. These are just rumors that announce it. People were contaminated in Mangina, died in Mangina and were buried in Mangina. At this stage, information that reaches us from different health structures, there is no case of Ebola virus at home in Ituri, not even a suspected case", quieted the governor.

In its bulletin published last [Sat 4 Aug 2018], the Ministry of Health announced that laboratories are already operational in several cities in the provinces of North Kivu, Tshopo and Ituri, to prevent the spread of the disease. In this regard, Abdallah Pene Mbaka urged his people not to consume dead game meat or bats. He urged all residents of Ituri to alert the health authorities of any suspected cases of vomiting or diarrhea in families.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail rapporteur Mary Marshall

